Generally, the system works pretty well, but there are a few weaknesses and annoyances:
1)  I've spent years (100's of man-hours, easily) developing my own test bank in Exam View (version 4 or 6 . . . not sure which), and Illuminate doesn't support importing Exam View bnk files.  
2)  I can't have Illuminate ignore erased marks.  When a kid changes his mind on a question and erases the old answer, the scanning software treats the MUCH fainter mark as part of a two-bubble response.  I need a settings option to ignore 2nd bubbles if they're below a certain relative faintness threshold.
3)  I never use the default webcam on my laptop, yet Illuminate always makes me wait for it to load in during scanning before I can switch to my USB document camera (an iPEVO VZ-R).  I'd like to set my iPEVO as my default camera so I don't have to go through that extra step.
